The null hypothesis for the normality test (Shapiro-Wilk) is: the sample data come from a normal distribution

## Data: data
## Models:
## mod2: Vcotyledon ~ Plateau + Zone + (1 | UniqueGeno)
## mod: Vcotyledon ~ Block + Plateau + Zone + (1 | UniqueGeno)
##      Df   AIC   BIC  logLik deviance  Chisq Chi Df Pr(>Chisq)
## mod2  7 17611 17657 -8798.5    17597                         
## mod   8 17612 17665 -8798.2    17596 0.6166      1     0.4323

p-value > 0.05, we cannot reject the null hypothesis. However, the Q-Q plot shows that the data probably don’t come from a normal distribution.
